The Shield of the Creed

	Philosophy

		-
			Repent from that which compels foul deeds; reject that which ignores those in need; and
			resist that which coerces belief.
		-

	Principles

		Purpose

			-
				The shield of the Creed is a maxim designed to distinguish and reinforce
				Angaianism, as well as analogous ideologies, against ideologies which are
				antagonistic to them.

				It can be invoked in the form of the three 'R's: "Repent, Reject, Resist".
			-